snippet.textDisplay:
C'mon, it was not that bad a movie.

- It nicely wrapped up all the plotlines of the other films in a heart felt ending that was a loving homage to the history of the series

- The acting in Star Wars movies has always prioritised non-verbal acting, physical acting and facial expressions over dialogue

- If thats ALL the ships the Resistance has left, thats not that many ships

-The threat only ended when the majority of the galaxy rebelled against the First Order

- The First Order got lots of soldiers by kidnapping children, mass cloning deceased loyal troops and having a small loyal group of elites that were raised on Exegal by cultists and ex-Imperials

- Palpatine cloned himself several times in the Expandee Universe. Every long time fan knew that was going to be a plot point. Also Snoke was probably created by Palpatine at least partly using his own DNA and cloning technology

- The "every Star Destroyer now has a Death Star laser" is a logical conclusion to the "Death Star technology keeps advancing" plot. Each movie showed a new improvement and/or variation in the technology (original Death Star, improved Death Star, planet sized jacked-up Death Star, bunker buster cannon made using Death Star technology.) Technology advanced enough over 30 years so that Death Star technology got small and cheap enough they could put a low end Death Star laser on each of the remaining Star Destroyers.

snippet.textDisplay:
I haven't seen the Rise of Skywalker yet so I could be way off, but here it goes:


The people behind these films don't seem to know how to use what they have. The Last Jedi was divisive but it left plot threads hanging that could have been expanded upon for the follow up movie -- like in the beginning, the Rebels forces were diminished and forced to retreat with the First Order on it's tail; how were the Rebels going to fight back without Leia and Luke? What will Finn do with the information he learned from DJ that there are arms dealers who are profiting from both sides of the conflict? What are the consequences of Finn and Rose busting up that casino for the super wealthy? What about that stable boy who was foreshadowed to be force sensitive? Stuff happened in the Last Jedi and that stuff had yet to be resolved.
